-- Cedeno Agrees to One-Year Deal With New York Mets, NYT Reports
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-01-07T05:55:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-07/cedeno-agrees-to-one-year-deal-with-new-york-mets-nyt-reports.html
Venezuelan infielder Ronny Cedeno has
agreed to a one-year contract worth $1.1 million with the  New
York Mets , the New York Times reported.  Cedeno, 28, may play second base if the Mets trade Daniel Murphy, or may be a backup middle infielder, the Times said.  Cedeno has played seven seasons with the  Chicago Cubs ,
Seattle Mariners and most recently the Pittsburgh Pirates,
batting .246.  The deal is contingent on Cedeno passing his physical,
according to MLB.com.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
